<div class="embed-content">

<div class="tailwind-container">

  <link rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="https://ca-dmv.cityinnovate.com/assets/tailwind-container-39aff895a3508d7b01066cd260ee83c3354dbeec99448ffea0e90bc43de54a32.css" data-turbolinks-track="reload" />

  <div class="max-w-screen-xl mx-auto pt-12 pb-16 sm:pt-16 sm:pb-10 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:pt-20 lg:pb-14 lg:px-8">
    <div class="md:grid md:grid-cols-12 md:gap-8">
        <div class="md:col-span-8">
          <div class="px-8 pt-12">
            <h4 class="text-2xl leading-8 font-extrabold text-gray-900 tracking-tight sm:text-3xl sm:leading-9">Challenge</h4>
            <div class="trix-content">
              The California Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV) is seeking a streamlined, automated, comprehensive, and robust solution to improve the current data gathering processes from divisions for resource and activity allocations, provide a faster model for the design of detailed activities for cost analysis purposes, and simplify the allocation calculation processes and data validation processes with automated calculations built-in for our Budget and Fiscal Analysis Branch.
              <ul>
<li>
<a href="https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/file/vendor-day-2022-presentation-pdf/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CA  DMV Vendor Day2022 Presentation PDF </a> </li>
<li>
<a href="https://cadmv.webex.com/recordingservice/sites/cadmv/recording/playback/95a8dcc67240103abb3f00505681e149" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CA DMV Vendor Day 2022 Event Recording</a> </li>
<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1yJWHV1XsEzy3syh4bOrWoYG428yvq-1a/view?usp=sharing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Current ABC Model Timeline Details</a></li>
</ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="px-8 pt-12">
            <h4 class="text-2xl leading-8 font-extrabold text-gray-900 tracking-tight sm:text-3xl sm:leading-9">Background</h4>
            <div class="trix-content">
              <p><span style="color:#414041;">The current system is a time-consuming process that lacks integration with a time tracking system and automation with workload and transaction reports. It is an outdated model that utilizes actual annual expenditures and a predominantly manual process of allocating resources to the identified activities and cost objects and is at its capacity for tracked activities.  </span></p><p>This results in:</p><ul>
<li>DMV spends 6,000 hours in labor annually to complete the current model</li>
<li>Eight months time to complete</li>
<li>Team spends less time on data analyses</li>
<li>Reports for management are not published frequent enough to aid with making informed business decisions</li>
</ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="px-8 pt-12">
            <h4 class="text-2xl leading-8 font-extrabold text-gray-900 tracking-tight sm:text-3xl sm:leading-9">Requirements & Outcome</h4>
            <div class="trix-content">
              <p>DMV is seeking a solution that is designed to assist the Department and control agencies in decision making on items such as:</p><ul>
<li>Fund appropriations</li>
<li>Budget development</li>
<li>Reimbursements</li>
<li>Cost analysis</li>
<li>Workload/resource shifts</li>
</ul><p>As well  as:</p><ul>
<li>Provide benchmarking tool</li>
<li>Integrate with time tracking solution and other data sources</li>
<li>Implementation by December 2022</li>
</ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-4">

